    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-27T00:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-27T00:30:00-05:00" n="274"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/12–2749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Burma</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Day</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rangoon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-27T12:00:00+06:30"
                            >December 27, 1949—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:48 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>562. Burmese Government opinion:</p>
                <p>Dominant Socialist group would welcome early or delayed recognition by US as
                    strengthening their position but Conservatives would see long-range disadvantage
                    in increasing prestige of regime that may invade or infiltrate into Burma.
                    Action would weaken belief that US is bulwark against communism and be regarded
                    proof US policy opportunistic.</p>
                <p>Indefinite withholding of recognition would reinforce respect for US as upholder
                    of law and democratic freedoms but would aggravate sense of insecurity from
                    rivalries major powers and incline Government Burma rely even more on
                    Commonwealth rather than US for aid.</p>
                <p>Burmese public opinion:</p>
                <p>Early or delayed recognition would be interpreted as evidence US not strong
                    enough follow independent course. As public susceptible to Communist or leftwing
                    Socialist propaganda derogatory to US, effective information program explaining
                    reasons would be desirable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Day</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
